Title: Series: Premier Liures des Paisages du Sieur Vendrecable
Description: Plate 6: The Flight into Egypt; Joseph in the front with Mary seated on a donkey, holding Christ and a city in the background; from a series of six prints Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Adriaen van der Cabel
Curator's comments: This state is not described in Hollstein and differs from the first state (for which see S. 2582) by the addition of a number 6 at the end of the lettering.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (13) (state not in Hollstein)
Acquisition notes: For the history of the acquisition of the Sheepshanks collection, please see Sheepshanks.1
